headlines.description: — Alperen Sengun had 22 points, 10 rebounds and 11 assists, Fred VanVleet added 27 points and 11 assists, and the Houston Rockets pulled out a 117-111 overtime win against the Minnesota Timberwolves in an NBA Cup game on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sengun records triple-double and Rockets beat Wolves 117-111 in OT to clinch NBA Cup group

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Utah Jazz

headlines.description: — Victor Wembanyama scored 34 points, rookie Stephon Castle matched a season high with 23 and the San Antonio Spurs beat the Utah Jazz 128-115 in an NBA Cup game on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wembanyama, Castle lead Spurs to 128-115 win over Jazz

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Phoenix Suns

headlines.description: — Bradley Beal and Kevin Durant each scored 23 points and the Phoenix Suns celebrated the healthy return of both players with a 127-100 win over the Los Angeles Lakers on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bradley Beal, Kevin Durant both return from injury, lead the Suns past the Lakers 127-100
